 g coconut milk, water, stock paste, lime leaves, fish sauce, lime juice and salt then cook <b>15 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid, then weigh in noodles. Cover noodles with boiling water and set aside to cook."},{"content":"Add chicken to mixing bowl and cook <b>7 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add prawns and pak choi then cook <b>4-5 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>, or until prawns are cooked through. Carefully remove kaffir lime leaves using a slotted spoon."},{"content":"Drain rice noodles through simmering basket and divide noodles evenly between 4 serving bowls. Pour laksa over the top."},{"content":"Garnish with bean sprouts, extra sliced chilli and extra coriander leaves before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To prepare coriander roots for use in the curry paste, remove all the fibrous small brown off-shoots from the main root by scraping with a teaspoon.","Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> for the chicken stock paste recipe.","Shrimp paste, also known as belachan, can be found in the International aisle of most supermarkets or specialty Asian grocers."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","40m","4 portions"]}